---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Impact"
	description="Quantitative outcomes across research infrastructure, education, workforce development, and grants."
>
	<h1>Impact</h1>
	<p class="intro">
		Numbers that represent real systems built, real people trained, and real research enabled.
	</p>

	<section>
		<h2>Research Infrastructure</h2>
		<ul class="metrics">
			<li><strong>1,603</strong> datasets published on UCLA Dataverse</li>
			<li><strong>54,655</strong> files archived</li>
			<li><strong>142,300+</strong> dataset downloads</li>
			<li><strong>2.9 PB</strong> of data processed through Redivis in 2024</li>
			<li><strong>2 minutes</strong> — Carceral Ecologies pipeline (down from 318 minutes)</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			UCLA Dataverse supports self-service data publishing across disciplines. Redivis provides
			a compliant, governed environment for restricted and sensitive datasets — P3/P4 data that
			had no institutional home before 2021.
		</p>
		<p>
			Two of UCLA's six <strong>2024 Public Impact Research Award</strong> winners were directly
			supported by DSC infrastructure and services.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Education & Training</h2>
		<ul class="metrics">
			<li><strong>28 workshops</strong> delivered through UC Carpentries</li>
			<li><strong>2,896 learners</strong> reached system-wide</li>
			<li><strong>10 campuses</strong> in the UC Carpentries network</li>
			<li><strong>14+</strong> open science lessons in development (IMLS)</li>
			<li><strong>500+</strong> annual learners at peak UC Carpentries scale</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			UC Carpentries delivers computational and data skills training across the UC system.
			The IMLS Open Science Curriculum trains librarians as open science educators — a
			train-the-trainers model that multiplies reach beyond any single institution.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Workforce Development</h2>
		<ul class="metrics">
			<li><strong>1,175</strong> documented service interactions</li>
			<li><strong>190</strong> consultations handled by DataSquad students (24%)</li>
			<li><strong>100%</strong> placement rate for a full DataSquad cohort</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			DataSquad trains undergraduates as research data consultants. Students contributed to
			award-winning research while gaining professional experience. The program force-multiplies
			DSC capacity without proportional staffing increases.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Grants & Funding</h2>
		<ul class="metrics">
			<li>
				<strong>$1,850,000</strong> — Sloan Foundation, UC OSPO Network (Co-PI, UCLA Lead)
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>$237,000</strong> — IMLS, Open Science Curriculum for Librarians (PI)
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			These grants reflect external validation of the work and fund programs with multi-campus
			and national reach.
		</p>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.intro {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	section {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding-bottom: 2rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	section:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}
	h2 {
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}
	.metrics {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
	}
	.metrics li {
		font-size: 1rem;
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.metrics li:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
	}
</style>
